head(ai)
ai.mas <- droplevels(subset(ai,sexe=="M"))
ai.fem <- droplevels(subset(ai,sexe=="F"))
ggplot(ai, aes(x = F2_6.Hz., y = F1_6.Hz., color = ton)) + 
    geom_point() + 
    stat_ellipse(level = 0.67) + 
    scale_x_reverse() + scale_y_reverse() +
    theme_classic() + 
    theme(legend.position = "none")

ai %>%
    summarize (mean_F1.20. = mean(F1_3.Hz.),
              mean_F2.20. = mean(F2_3.Hz.),
              mean_F1.30. = mean(F1_4.Hz.),
              mean_F2.30. = mean(F2_4.Hz.),
              mean_F1.40. = mean(F1_5.Hz.),
              mean_F2.40. = mean(F2_5.Hz.),
              mean_F1.50. = mean(F1_6.Hz.),
              mean_F2.50. = mean(F2_6.Hz.),
              mean_F1.60. = mean(F1_7.Hz.),
              mean_F2.60. = mean(F2_7.Hz.),
              mean_F1.70. = mean(F1_8.Hz.),
              mean_F2.70. = mean(F2_8.Hz.),
              mean_F1.80. = mean(F1_9.Hz.),
              mean_F2.80. = mean(F2_9.Hz.))
ai_means.mas <- ai.mas %>%
    group_by(ton) %>%
    summarize_at(vars(F1_1.Hz.:F2_11.Hz.), mean, na.rm = TRUE)
ai_means.fem <- ai.fem %>%
    group_by(ton) %>%
    summarize_at(vars(F1_1.Hz.:F2_11.Hz.), mean, na.rm = TRUE)
print(ai_means.mas)
